To attach methods to a struct, we use an `impl` (implementation) block.

```rust
struct Rectangle {
    width: u32,
    height: u32,
}

impl Rectangle {
    // We'll write methods here!
}
```

The defining feature of a method is that its completely required first parameter is named `&self` (a reference to the struct instance it is being called on).

```rust
impl Rectangle {
    fn area(&self) -> u32 {
        self.width * self.height
    }
}
```
